review_text:
This place looks like the place to be come summer, with a generous splash pad, a dozen or so picnic tables and grills, a wide field, and tons of hiking trails.

I will say though...hunting?!?!  I am not anti-hunting, but it would be nice to know it wasn't a possibility year-round at a state park.  It literally says to wear bright colors so you don't get shot!

Other than THAT, which I have no insider knowledge of how prevalent it is or not, I really enjoyed my trip.

I especially liked that all dogs I saw were leashed, which is a rule at DCR parks, but not always enforced or followed.  Thank you!!!!

And there are bathrooms open, but they closed well before the park did.

Cool history and very accessible.  Even the trails aren't super bumpy.
I came here looking for pukwudgie and any other Bridgewater Triangle spooks and goblins. I heard some strange noises, but did not see any tiny humanoids. Still a great walk through the forest though!
I have been coming here since I was a kid, when you had the pool. I find it very peaceful and great for the kids and pets.

Great place to take children of all ages! Amazing hiking/walking trails. If you like the nature and everything that comes with it you'll love the trails. Also has a wading pool for children and parents. They also have sites where you can set up for the day with charcoal grills. Bathrooms on site.
They allow hunting here so just be careful.  Beautiful place for hiking.

Pretty good hike! There's definite evidence of extracurricular activities in the forest, but don't let that stop you from climbing to the top of profile rock or exploring the trails. Tons of evergreen trees. Pictures are of the view from the top of the rock. Be careful as private property does border the forest in several locations

Nice place to hike in the summer, fall, winter, and spring dont get lost however use maps if needed, I was able to still get celluar service on cell phone throughout the trails. You would also see motorcross bike trails as well, and occasional wildlife. Great place to barbecue with picnic benches and if you have kids it have a nice waddling pool for small children.

Update,
Folks I drive a Acura rsx. A little sports coupe. I drove through every single trail this park had to offer. It's all totally accessible, and the pot holes are a test of your skills and mettle as a driver. the peace of mind is unreal and you see absolutely no one. Let alone its a major part of the "bridge water triangle" get in here folks and live !

Absolutely love taking my 3 year old here! Pack a picnic blanket and some snacks and could spend our whole day here. Warming off in the sun and enjoy the nice grass space or the picnic tables for some midday lunch! Definitely being sunscreen and some bug spray as a lot of woods are around!

Found this place like 4 years ago and it was amazing. It was a shallow Wade pool with a big water flowing mushroom and other things but now it's a sad, flat, wet cement like surface with random water spraying. Guess it's still fun for the little ones to cool off a bit but compared to what it was before it's extremely underwhelming . I'm so sad lol

Absolutely Love this Location ... They keep the Wading pool clean every few hours! GREAT for kids 3months-10yrs ... its 1.5 ft sitting area inside and grills around the park. Been are our family quick play fun spot.... Adventure in the woods and swimming for the kids.

So cute for little kids to safely play. The life guards are on point with everything and are always keeping everyone safe. The only problem is I noticed that people use the life guards as babysitters! They are not getting paid to babysit the splash pad is NOT a free daycare.

Perfect for toddlers and non swimmers. A bit crowded and the later in the day the less parking available. There are picnic tables and grills around which is nice, and actual bathrooms (which usually have very wet floors). I'd recommend bug spray and water shoes for the cement floor of the wading pool.

UPDATE - TEMPORARILY CLOSED FOR CONSTRUCTION UMTIL NEXT SUMMER 2022

This is a great place that's close by to bring kids, I went last year and the year before but may try today as I'm not sure about any new guidelines because of covid. Last year there was one other child there when we went so no problems whatsoever. The year before we showed up just as they were having everyone leave so it was actually a good time because some people end up leaving at that time. I never had an issue with over crowding and not being able to get in but it could be because I have not gone on a weekend, but I'm not sure. I will update once go this year.

My kids love this place. It gets a little busy certain times, and they close down for about 20 every few hours to filter the pool. It's seasonal too, starts up in late May and closes down around early September. It has public restrooms, and a Pagoda with tables for picnics. Very nice place.
Willette's Optical Paradise Approved!
Does anyone know when the splash pad opens ?
Miss the tennis court but great look now
